            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EHeman's%20fourteen%20sons%20were%20given%20to%20him%20through%20the%20promises%20of%20God%20to%20honor%20him%20(1%20Chronicles%2025%3A5%20NIV).%20The%20Bible%20records%20that%20Heman's%20children%20were%20the%20product%20of%20his%20faith%20in%20the%20promises%20of%20God.%20Heman%20received%20these%20gifts%20by%20believing%20that%20God%20would%20give%20him%20children%20and%20that%20they%20would%20be%20a%20blessing.%20These%20fourteen%20sons%20were%20all%20gifted%20in%20music%2C%20and%20their%20excellence%20served%20to%20honor%20their%20father%20(1%20Chronicles%2025%3A5-7).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIn%20the%20New%20Testament%2C%20we%20also%20see%20this%20same%20pattern%20of%20godly%20children%20that%20are%20a%20blessing%20to%20their%20parents.%20Philip%20had%20four%20virgin%20daughters%20who%20prophesied%20and%20whose%20ministry%20was%20a%20great%20reflection%20on%20Philip's%20family%20and%20life.%20His%20children%2C%20like%20Heman's%2C%20brought%20honor%20to%20their%20father's%20name.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20children%20of%20the%20godly%20are%20a%20blessing%20(Psalm%2037%3A26).%20They%20are%20a%20gift-not%20a%20curse!%20Our%20children%20have%20been%20given%20to%20us%20by%20the%20promises%20of%20God%2C%20and%20Satan%20cannot%20use%20their%20lives%20to%20bring%20us%20shame%20and%20dishonor.%20Secure%20in%20the%20promises%20of%20God%2C%20we%20should%20expect%20our%20children%20to%20honor%20us%2C%20not%20to%20embarrass%20us.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ELet%20us%20expect%20all%20our%20children%20to%20know%20and%20serve%20the%20Lord%20and%20to%20bring%20us%20great%20delight%20as%20they%20walk%20before%20Him%20with%20all%20their%20hearts!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
