            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E1%20Chronicles%2024%3A1-26%3A11%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_24_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E1%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDuties%20of%20the%20Priests%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20is%20how%20Aaron%26%23x2019%3Bs%20descendants%2C%20the%20priests%2C%20were%20divided%20into%20groups%20for%20service.%20The%20sons%20of%20Aaron%20were%20Nadab%2C%20Abihu%2C%20Eleazar%2C%20and%20Ithamar.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_24_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Nadab%20and%20Abihu%20died%20before%20their%20father%2C%20and%20they%20had%20no%20sons.%20So%20only%20Eleazar%20and%20Ithamar%20were%20left%20to%20carry%20on%20as%20priests.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_24_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EWith%20the%20help%20of%20Zadok%2C%20who%20was%20a%20descendant%20of%20Eleazar%2C%20and%20of%20Ahimelech%2C%20who%20was%20a%20descendant%20of%20Ithamar%2C%20David%20divided%20Aaron%26%23x2019%3Bs%20descendants%20into%20groups%20according%20to%20their%20various%20duties.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_24_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EEleazar%26%23x2019%3Bs%20descendants%20were%20divided%20into%20sixteen%20groups%20and%20Ithamar%26%23x2019%3Bs%20into%20eight%2C%20for%20there%20were%20more%20family%20leaders%20among%20the%20descendants%20of%20Eleazar.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_24_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EAll%20tasks%20were%20assigned%20to%20the%20various%20groups%20by%20means%20of%20sacred%20lots%20so%20that%20no%20preference%20would%20be%20shown%2C%20for%20there%20were%20many%20qualified%20officials%20serving%20God%20in%20the%20sanctuary%20from%20among%20the%20descendants%20of%20both%20Eleazar%20and%20Ithamar.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_24_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EShemaiah%20son%20of%20Nethanel%2C%20a%20Levite%2C%20acted%20as%20secretary%20and%20wrote%20down%20the%20names%20and%20assignments%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20king%2C%20the%20officials%2C%20Zadok%20the%20priest%2C%20Ahimelech%20son%20of%20Abiathar%2C%20and%20the%20family%20leaders%20of%20the%20priests%20and%20Levites.%20The%20descendants%20of%20Eleazar%20and%20Ithamar%20took%20turns%20casting%20lots.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_24_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22list-vn-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20first%20lot%20fell%20to%20Jehoiarib.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22list%22%3EThe%20second%20lot%20fell%20to%20Jedaiah.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_24_8%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22list-vn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20third%20lot%20fell%20to%20Harim.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22list%22%3EThe%20fourth%20lot%20fell%20to%20Seorim.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_24_9%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22list-vn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20fifth%20lot%20fell%